<h1 align="center" class="style3">Inherent Parallelism </h1>
<ul type="disc">
  <li class="style7">&quot;Dataflow&quot; principle
    <ul>
      <li>A node executes only when it receives all of its inputs</li>
      <li>A node releases all its outputs at the same time when the node has completely finished execution </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li class="style7">This has the effect of forcing sequential execution between nodes that are data-dependent on one another</li>
  <li class="style7">Conversely, if no data-dependency exists - no wires, and the icons execute in parallel </li>
</ul>
